                    <comment id="12379962" author="becke@u.washington.edu" created="Wed, 16 Jul 2003 10:45:01 +0100"  >Created an attachment (id=7321)&lt;br/&gt;
Patch 1&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12379963" author="becke@u.washington.edu" created="Wed, 16 Jul 2003 10:46:05 +0100"  >If/when we make the move here&amp;#39;s a patch that moves Base64 and URL encoding to codec.</comment>
                    <comment id="12379964" author="olegk" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2003 03:08:31 +0000"  >Created an attachment (id=9600)&lt;br/&gt;
Patch 2&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12379965" author="olegk" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2003 03:15:54 +0000"  >With Codec 1.2 officially released, I think it is time we finally migrated to&lt;br/&gt;
Commons Codec framework. I want to see those warning messages finally go away&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Mike, I took liberty of creating a new patch as the one you posted a while ago&lt;br/&gt;
was outdated by now. I hope you do not mind (I was at the client basically to&lt;br/&gt;
watch another fella do all the work and I did not know what to do with my idle&lt;br/&gt;
time there).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
                    <comment id="12379966" author="becke@u.washington.edu" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2003 10:27:28 +0000"  >Oleg,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
No worries.  I&amp;#39;m glad this one is finally moving forward.  I think the patch is missing a few things &lt;br/&gt;
though.  Base64 is still there, and EncodingUtil.formUrlEncode() needs to make use of the codec. &lt;br/&gt;
Other than that it looks good to me.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Now that we&amp;#39;re making this move to codec, what do we want to do about the codec jar.  Do we &lt;br/&gt;
want to add it to CVS ala commons-logging?  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Mike</comment>
                    <comment id="12379967" author="olegk" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2003 18:52:43 +0000"  >Mike, good catch. I&amp;#39;ll make the corrections necessary before committing the&lt;br/&gt;
patch. As to committing commons-codec.jar to the CVS I do not have a strong&lt;br/&gt;
opinion on that. At the very least we should be consistent. We should either add&lt;br/&gt;
commons-codec.jar or remove commons-logging.jar. I can live with either scenario.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Any votes for or against keeping dependencies in the CVS?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
                    <comment id="12379968" author="oglueck" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2003 19:01:16 +0000"  >Please keep libraries inside CVS. This ensures you have the right version of the&lt;br/&gt;
library that matches the code. Getting a certain version of an external library&lt;br/&gt;
may become very difficult later in time! Sure there is Maven but still I&lt;br/&gt;
strongly discourage removing referenced libraries from the source tree.</comment>
                    <comment id="12379969" author="olegk" created="Fri, 19 Dec 2003 03:08:40 +0000"  >Created an attachment (id=9631)&lt;br/&gt;
Patch 3&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="12379970" author="olegk" created="Fri, 19 Dec 2003 03:10:22 +0000"  >The patch incorporates corrections suggested by Mike. If nobody complains&lt;br/&gt;
loudly, I&amp;#39;ll commit the patch tomorrow around 20:00GMT&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
                    <comment id="12379971" author="olegk" created="Wed, 7 Jan 2004 04:18:16 +0000"  >Patch committed. I have also updated the build script and added commoms-codec.jar &lt;br/&gt;
to the lib directory&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg</comment>
